The paper focuses on deep learning for tumor classification in histopathology, which is a computer vision task, suggesting that cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the impact of data augmentation and normalization on performance and learned representations, which are topics commonly studied in machine learning (cs.LG and cs.AI). The paper also introduces a novel measure for evaluating the distance between domains, which is related to domain adaptation (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning for classification in histopathology, which is a topic in natural language processing (cs.CL).
